@RSky Car Ok, yes it appears that you must be using Python 2.7, 3.4, 3.5, or 3.6. TensorFlow is not yet suporting 3.7 based on this:
https://www.tensorflow.org/install/pip
You can make a virtual environment (Virtualenv) that runs Python 3.6 on the same machine you're currently working on, and then do the TensorFlow.js stuff in that virtual env. The link above links to more about virtual environments if you're not familiar, but here it is also: https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/stable/

